#. <section class="sutta" id="mn10"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn10:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 10"
msgstr "Middle Discourses 10"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn10:0.2"
msgid "Satipaṭṭhānasutta"
msgstr "Mindfulness Meditation"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya1"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "mn10:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kurūsu viharati kammāsadhammaṃ nāma kurūnaṃ nigamo."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Kurus, near the Kuru "
"town named Kammāsadamma."

msgctxt "mn10:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "mn10:1.4"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti."
msgstr "“Mendicants!”"

msgctxt "mn10:1.5"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "mn10:1.6"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya2"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.56"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Ekāyano ayaṃ, bhikkhave, maggo sattānaṃ visuddhiyā, sokaparidevānaṃ "
"samatikkamāya, dukkhadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamāya, ñāyassa adhigamāya, "
"nibbānassa sacchikiriyāya, yadidaṃ cattāro satipaṭṭhānā."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, the four kinds of mindfulness meditation are the path to "
"convergence. They are in order to purify sentient beings, to get past sorrow "
"and crying, to make an end of pain and sadness, to complete the procedure, "
"and to realize extinguishment."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya3"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:3.1"
msgid "Katame cattāro?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "mn10:3.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, "
"vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body—keen, "
"aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world."

msgctxt "mn10:3.3"
msgid ""
"vedanāsu vedanānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke "
"abhijjhādomanassaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"They meditate observing an aspect of feelings—keen, aware, and mindful, rid "
"of desire and aversion for the world."

msgctxt "mn10:3.4"
msgid ""
"citte cittānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke "
"abhijjhādomanassaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"They meditate observing an aspect of the mind—keen, aware, and mindful, rid "
"of desire and aversion for the world."

msgctxt "mn10:3.5"
msgid ""
"dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke "
"abhijjhādomanassaṃ."
msgstr ""
"They meditate observing an aspect of principles—keen, aware, and mindful, "
"rid of desire and aversion for the world."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn10:3.6"
msgid "Uddeso niṭṭhito."
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "mn10:3.7"
msgid "1. Kāyānupassanā"
msgstr "1. Observing the Body"

#. </h2><h3>
msgctxt "mn10:3.8"
msgid "1.1. Kāyānupassanāānāpānapabba"
msgstr "1.1. Mindfulness of Breathing"

#. </h3><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya4"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:4.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati?"
msgstr "And how does a mendicant meditate observing an aspect of the body?"

msgctxt "mn10:4.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu araññagato vā rukkhamūlagato vā suññāgāragato vā "
"nisīdati, pallaṅkaṃ ābhujitvā, ujuṃ kāyaṃ paṇidhāya, parimukhaṃ satiṃ "
"upaṭṭhapetvā."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant—gone to a wilderness, or to the root of a tree, or to "
"an empty hut—sits down cross-legged, with their body straight, and focuses "
"their mindfulness right there."

#. VAR: satova → sato (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "mn10:4.3"
msgid "So satova assasati, satova passasati."
msgstr "Just mindful, they breathe in. Mindful, they breathe out."

msgctxt "mn10:4.4"
msgid ""
"Dīghaṃ vā assasanto ‘dīghaṃ assasāmī’ti pajānāti, dīghaṃ vā passasanto ‘"
"dīghaṃ passasāmī’ti pajānāti, "
msgstr ""
"When breathing in heavily they know: ‘I’m breathing in heavily.’ When "
"breathing out heavily they know: ‘I’m breathing out heavily.’ "

msgctxt "mn10:4.5"
msgid ""
"rassaṃ vā assasanto ‘rassaṃ assasāmī’ti pajānāti, rassaṃ vā passasanto ‘"
"rassaṃ passasāmī’ti pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"When breathing in lightly they know: ‘I’m breathing in lightly.’ When "
"breathing out lightly they know: ‘I’m breathing out lightly.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:4.6"
msgid ""
"‘Sabbakāyapaṭisaṃvedī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘sabbakāyapaṭisaṃvedī "
"passasissāmī’ti sikkhati."
msgstr ""
"They practice breathing in experiencing the whole body. They practice "
"breathing out experiencing the whole body."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:4.7"
msgid ""
"‘Passambhayaṃ kāyasaṅkhāraṃ assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘passambhayaṃ "
"kāyasaṅkhāraṃ passasissāmī’ti sikkhati."
msgstr ""
"They practice breathing in stilling the body’s motion. They practice "
"breathing out stilling the body’s motion."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:4.8"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, dakkho bhamakāro vā bhamakārantevāsī vā dīghaṃ vā "
"añchanto ‘dīghaṃ añchāmī’ti pajānāti, rassaṃ vā añchanto ‘rassaṃ añchāmī’ti "
"pajānāti;"
msgstr ""
"It’s like an expert carpenter or carpenter’s apprentice. When making a deep "
"cut they know: ‘I’m making a deep cut,’ and when making a shallow cut they "
"know: ‘I’m making a shallow cut.’"

msgctxt "mn10:4.9"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dīghaṃ vā assasanto ‘dīghaṃ assasāmī’ti "
"pajānāti, dīghaṃ vā passasanto ‘dīghaṃ passasāmī’ti pajānāti, rassaṃ vā "
"assasanto ‘rassaṃ assasāmī’ti pajānāti, rassaṃ vā passasanto ‘rassaṃ "
"passasāmī’ti pajānāti;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn10:4.10"
msgid ""
"‘sabbakāyapaṭisaṃvedī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘sabbakāyapaṭisaṃvedī "
"passasissāmī’ti sikkhati;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn10:4.11"
msgid ""
"‘passambhayaṃ kāyasaṅkhāraṃ assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘passambhayaṃ "
"kāyasaṅkhāraṃ passasissāmī’ti sikkhati."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya5"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:5.1"
msgid ""
"Iti ajjhattaṃ vā kāye kāyānupassī viharati, bahiddhā vā kāye kāyānupassī "
"viharati, ajjhattabahiddhā vā kāye kāyānupassī viharati;"
msgstr ""
"And so they meditate observing an aspect of the body internally, externally, "
"and both internally and externally."

msgctxt "mn10:5.2"
msgid ""
"samudayadhammānupassī vā kāyasmiṃ viharati, vayadhammānupassī vā kāyasmiṃ "
"viharati, samudayavayadhammānupassī vā kāyasmiṃ viharati."
msgstr ""
"They meditate observing the body as liable to originate, as liable to "
"vanish, and as liable to both originate and vanish."

msgctxt "mn10:5.3"
msgid ""
"‘Atthi kāyo’ti vā panassa sati paccupaṭṭhitā hoti. Yāvadeva ñāṇamattāya "
"paṭissatimattāya anissito ca viharati, na ca kiñci loke upādiyati."
msgstr ""
"Or mindfulness is established that the body exists, to the extent necessary "
"for knowledge and mindfulness. They meditate independent, not grasping at "
"anything in the world."

#. VAR: Evampi kho → evampi (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "mn10:5.4"
msgid "Evampi kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati."
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn10:5.5"
msgid "Ānāpānapabbaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "mn10:5.6"
msgid "1.2. Kāyānupassanāiriyāpathapabba"
msgstr "1.2. The Postures"

#. </h3><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya6"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.57"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:6.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu gacchanto vā ‘gacchāmī’ti pajānāti, ṭhito "
"vā ‘ṭhitomhī’ti pajānāti, nisinno vā ‘nisinnomhī’ti pajānāti, sayāno vā "
"‘sayānomhī’ti pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, when a mendicant is walking they know: ‘I am walking.’ When "
"standing they know: ‘I am standing.’ When sitting they know: ‘I am sitting.’ "
"And when lying down they know: ‘I am lying down.’"

msgctxt "mn10:6.2"
msgid "Yathā yathā vā panassa kāyo paṇihito hoti tathā tathā naṃ pajānāti."
msgstr "Whatever posture their body is in, they know it."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya7"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:7.1"
msgid ""
"Iti ajjhattaṃ vā kāye kāyānupassī viharati, bahiddhā vā kāye kāyānupassī "
"viharati, ajjhattabahiddhā vā kāye kāyānupassī viharati;"
msgstr ""
"And so they meditate observing an aspect of the body internally, externally, "
"and both internally and externally."

msgctxt "mn10:7.2"
msgid ""
"samudayadhammānupassī vā kāyasmiṃ viharati, vayadhammānupassī vā kāyasmiṃ "
"viharati, samudayavayadhammānupassī vā kāyasmiṃ viharati."
msgstr ""
"They meditate observing the body as liable to originate, as liable to "
"vanish, and as liable to both originate and vanish."

msgctxt "mn10:7.3"
msgid ""
"‘Atthi kāyo’ti vā panassa sati paccupaṭṭhitā hoti. Yāvadeva ñāṇamattāya "
"paṭissatimattāya anissito ca viharati, na ca kiñci loke upādiyati."
msgstr ""
"Or mindfulness is established that the body exists, to the extent necessary "
"for knowledge and mindfulness. They meditate independent, not grasping at "
"anything in the world."

msgctxt "mn10:7.4"
msgid "Evampi kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati."
msgstr ""
"That too is how a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn10:7.5"
msgid "Iriyāpathapabbaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "mn10:7.6"
msgid "1.3. Kāyānupassanāsampajānapabba"
msgstr "1.3. Situational Awareness"

#. </h3><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya8"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:8.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu abhikkante paṭikkante sampajānakārī hoti, "
"ālokite vilokite sampajānakārī hoti, samiñjite pasārite sampajānakārī hoti, "
"saṅghāṭipattacīvaradhāraṇe sampajānakārī hoti, asite pīte khāyite sāyite "
"sampajānakārī hoti, uccārapassāvakamme sampajānakārī hoti, gate ṭhite "
"nisinne sutte jāgarite bhāsite tuṇhībhāve sampajānakārī hoti."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant acts with situational awareness when going out and "
"coming back; when looking ahead and aside; when bending and extending the "
"limbs; when bearing the outer robe, bowl and robes; when eating, drinking, "
"chewing, and tasting; when urinating and defecating; when walking, standing, "
"sitting, sleeping, waking, speaking, and keeping silent."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya9"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:9.1"
msgid "Iti ajjhattaṃ vā kāye kāyānupassī viharati … pe …"
msgstr "And so they meditate observing an aspect of the body internally …"

msgctxt "mn10:9.2"
msgid "evampi kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati."
msgstr ""
"That too is how a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn10:9.3"
msgid "Sampajānapabbaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "mn10:9.4"
msgid "1.4. Kāyānupassanāpaṭikūlamanasikārapabba"
msgstr "1.4. Focusing on the Repulsive"

#. </h3><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya10"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:10.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu imameva kāyaṃ uddhaṃ pādatalā, adho "
"kesamatthakā, tacapariyantaṃ pūraṃ nānappakārassa asucino paccavekkhati:"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant examines their own body, up from the soles of the "
"feet and down from the tips of the hairs, wrapped in skin and full of many "
"kinds of filth."

#. VAR: nhāru → nahāru (bj, pts1) | nahārū (s1-3)
#. VAR: siṅghāṇikā lasikā muttan’ti → muttaṃ matthaluṅganti (mr)
msgctxt "mn10:10.2"
msgid ""
"‘atthi imasmiṃ kāye kesā lomā nakhā dantā taco maṃsaṃ nhāru aṭṭhi "
"aṭṭhimiñjaṃ vakkaṃ hadayaṃ yakanaṃ kilomakaṃ pihakaṃ papphāsaṃ antaṃ "
"antaguṇaṃ udariyaṃ karīsaṃ pittaṃ semhaṃ pubbo lohitaṃ sedo medo assu vasā "
"kheḷo siṅghāṇikā lasikā muttan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘In this body there is head hair, body hair, nails, teeth, skin, flesh, "
"sinews, bones, bone marrow, kidneys, heart, liver, diaphragm, spleen, lungs, "
"intestines, mesentery, undigested food, feces, bile, phlegm, pus, blood, "
"sweat, fat, tears, grease, saliva, snot, synovial fluid, urine.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
#. VAR: putoḷi → mūtoḷī (bj, s1-3) | mutoḷī (pts1)
msgctxt "mn10:10.3"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, ubhatomukhā putoḷi pūrā nānāvihitassa dhaññassa, "
"seyyathidaṃ—sālīnaṃ vīhīnaṃ muggānaṃ māsānaṃ tilānaṃ taṇḍulānaṃ. Tamenaṃ "
"cakkhumā puriso muñcitvā paccavekkheyya: ‘ime sālī ime vīhī ime muggā ime "
"māsā ime tilā ime taṇḍulā’ti."
msgstr ""
"It’s as if there were a bag with openings at both ends, filled with various "
"kinds of grains, such as fine rice, wheat, mung beans, peas, sesame, and "
"ordinary rice. And someone with good eyesight were to open it and examine "
"the contents: ‘These grains are fine rice, these are wheat, these are mung "
"beans, these are peas, these are sesame, and these are ordinary rice.’"

msgctxt "mn10:10.4"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu imameva kāyaṃ uddhaṃ pādatalā, adho "
"kesamatthakā, tacapariyantaṃ pūraṃ nānappakārassa asucino paccavekkhati:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn10:10.5"
msgid "‘atthi imasmiṃ kāye kesā lomā … pe … muttan’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya11"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:11.1"
msgid "Iti ajjhattaṃ vā kāye kāyānupassī viharati … pe …"
msgstr "And so they meditate observing an aspect of the body internally …"

msgctxt "mn10:11.2"
msgid "evampi kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati."
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn10:11.3"
msgid "Paṭikūlamanasikārapabbaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "mn10:11.4"
msgid "1.5. Kāyānupassanādhātumanasikārapabba"
msgstr "1.5. Focusing on the Elements"

#. </h3><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya12"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:12.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu imameva kāyaṃ yathāṭhitaṃ yathāpaṇihitaṃ "
"dhātuso paccavekkhati:"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant examines their own body, whatever its placement or "
"posture, according to the elements:"

msgctxt "mn10:12.2"
msgid "‘atthi imasmiṃ kāye pathavīdhātu āpodhātu tejodhātu vāyodhātū’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘In this body there is the earth element, the water element, the fire "
"element, and the air element.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.58"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
#. VAR: catumahāpathe → cātummahāpathe (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "mn10:12.3"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, dakkho goghātako vā goghātakantevāsī vā gāviṃ "
"vadhitvā catumahāpathe bilaso vibhajitvā nisinno assa."
msgstr ""
"It’s as if an expert butcher or butcher’s apprentice were to kill a cow and "
"sit down at the crossroads with the meat cut into portions."

msgctxt "mn10:12.4"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu imameva kāyaṃ yathāṭhitaṃ yathāpaṇihitaṃ "
"dhātuso paccavekkhati:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn10:12.5"
msgid "‘atthi imasmiṃ kāye pathavīdhātu āpodhātu tejodhātu vāyodhātū’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya13"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc18"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:13.1"
msgid "Iti ajjhattaṃ vā kāye kāyānupassī viharati … pe …"
msgstr "And so they meditate observing an aspect of the body internally …"

msgctxt "mn10:13.2"
msgid "evampi kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati."
msgstr ""
"That too is how a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn10:13.3"
msgid "Dhātumanasikārapabbaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "mn10:13.4"
msgid "1.6. Kāyānupassanānavasivathikapabba"
msgstr "1.6. The Charnel Ground Contemplations"

#. </h3><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya14"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc19"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:14.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu seyyathāpi passeyya sarīraṃ sivathikāya "
"chaḍḍitaṃ ekāhamataṃ vā dvīhamataṃ vā tīhamataṃ vā uddhumātakaṃ vinīlakaṃ "
"vipubbakajātaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, suppose a mendicant were to see a corpse discarded in a charnel "
"ground. And it had been dead for one, two, or three days, bloated, livid, "
"and festering."

# This context makes it clear what the idiom “imameva kayam” really means.
msgctxt "mn10:14.2"
msgid "So imameva kāyaṃ upasaṃharati:"
msgstr "They’d compare it with their own body:"

msgctxt "mn10:14.3"
msgid "‘ayampi kho kāyo evaṃdhammo evaṃbhāvī evaṃanatīto’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘This body is also of that same nature, that same kind, and cannot go beyond "
"that.’ "

#. <a class="nya" id="nya15"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:15.1"
msgid "Iti ajjhattaṃ vā kāye kāyānupassī viharati … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn10:15.2"
msgid "evampi kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati. (1)"
msgstr ""
"That too is how a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya16"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc20"></a>
#. VAR: kulalehi vā khajjamānaṃ gijjhehi vā khajjamānaṃ kaṅkehi vā khajjamānaṃ sunakhehi vā khajjamānaṃ byagghehi vā khajjamānaṃ dīpīhi vā khajjamānaṃ siṅgālehi vā → kulalehi vā khajjamānaṃ gijjhehi vā khajjamānaṃ supāṇehi vā khajjamānaṃ sigālehi vā (sī1, pā1), gijjhehi vā khajjamānaṃ kulalalehi vā khajjamānaṃ suvāṇehi vā khajjamānaṃ siṇigālehi vā (syā1-3)
msgctxt "mn10:16.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu seyyathāpi passeyya sarīraṃ sivathikāya "
"chaḍḍitaṃ kākehi vā khajjamānaṃ kulalehi vā khajjamānaṃ gijjhehi vā "
"khajjamānaṃ kaṅkehi vā khajjamānaṃ sunakhehi vā khajjamānaṃ byagghehi vā "
"khajjamānaṃ dīpīhi vā khajjamānaṃ siṅgālehi vā khajjamānaṃ vividhehi vā "
"pāṇakajātehi khajjamānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, suppose they were to see a corpse discarded in a charnel ground "
"being devoured by crows, hawks, vultures, herons, dogs, tigers, leopards, "
"jackals, and many kinds of little creatures."

msgctxt "mn10:16.2"
msgid "So imameva kāyaṃ upasaṃharati:"
msgstr "They’d compare it with their own body:"

msgctxt "mn10:16.3"
msgid "‘ayampi kho kāyo evaṃdhammo evaṃbhāvī evaṃanatīto’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘This body is also of that same nature, that same kind, and cannot go beyond "
"that.’"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya17"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:17.1"
msgid "Iti ajjhattaṃ vā kāye kāyānupassī viharati … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn10:17.2"
msgid "evampi kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati. (2)"
msgstr ""
"That too is how a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya18-23"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc21"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:18-23.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu seyyathāpi passeyya sarīraṃ sivathikāya "
"chaḍḍitaṃ aṭṭhikasaṅkhalikaṃ samaṃsalohitaṃ nhārusambandhaṃ … pe … (3)"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, suppose they were to see a corpse discarded in a charnel "
"ground, a skeleton with flesh and blood, held together by sinews …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc22"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:18-23.2"
msgid "Aṭṭhikasaṅkhalikaṃ nimaṃsalohitamakkhitaṃ nhārusambandhaṃ … pe … (4)"
msgstr ""
"A skeleton without flesh but smeared with blood, and held together by sinews "
"…"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc23"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:18-23.3"
msgid "Aṭṭhikasaṅkhalikaṃ apagatamaṃsalohitaṃ nhārusambandhaṃ … pe … (5)"
msgstr "A skeleton rid of flesh and blood, held together by sinews …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya24"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc24"></a>
#. VAR: aññena phāsukaṭṭhikaṃ aññena piṭṭhiṭṭhikaṃ aññena khandhaṭṭhikaṃ → aññena piṭṭhikaṇṭakaṃ aññena ­piṭṭhi­kaṇ­ṭakaṭ­ṭhi­kaṃ aññena phāsukaṭṭhikaṃ aññena uraṭṭhikaṃ aññena bāhuṭṭhikaṃ aññena aṃsaṭṭhikaṃ (syā1-3), aññena kaṭaṭṭhikaṃ aññena piṭṭhikaṇṭakaṃ (pā1)
#. VAR: aññena gīvaṭṭhikaṃ aññena hanukaṭṭhikaṃ aññena dantaṭṭhikaṃ aññena sīsakaṭāhaṃ → aññena sīsakaṭāhaṃ (sī1)
msgctxt "mn10:24.1"
msgid ""
"Aṭṭhikāni apagatasambandhāni disā vidisā vikkhittāni, aññena hatthaṭṭhikaṃ "
"aññena pādaṭṭhikaṃ aññena gopphakaṭṭhikaṃ aññena jaṅghaṭṭhikaṃ aññena "
"ūruṭṭhikaṃ aññena kaṭiṭṭhikaṃ aññena phāsukaṭṭhikaṃ aññena piṭṭhiṭṭhikaṃ "
"aññena khandhaṭṭhikaṃ aññena gīvaṭṭhikaṃ aññena hanukaṭṭhikaṃ aññena "
"dantaṭṭhikaṃ aññena sīsakaṭāhaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Bones rid of sinews scattered in every direction. Here a hand-bone, there a "
"foot-bone, here a shin-bone, there a thigh-bone, here a hip-bone, there a "
"rib-bone, here a back-bone, there an arm-bone, here a neck-bone, there a jaw-"
"bone, here a tooth, there the skull …"

msgctxt "mn10:24.2"
msgid "So imameva kāyaṃ upasaṃharati:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn10:24.3"
msgid "‘ayampi kho kāyo evaṃdhammo evaṃbhāvī evaṃanatīto’ti."
msgstr ""

#. <a class="nya" id="nya25"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:25.1"
msgid "Iti ajjhattaṃ vā kāye kāyānupassī viharati … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn10:25.2"
msgid "evampi kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati. (6)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya26-28"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc25"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:26-28.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu seyyathāpi passeyya sarīraṃ sivathikāya "
"chaḍḍitaṃ, aṭṭhikāni setāni saṅkhavaṇṇapaṭibhāgāni … pe … (7)"
msgstr "White bones, the color of shells …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya29"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc26"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:29.1"
msgid "Aṭṭhikāni puñjakitāni terovassikāni … pe … (8)"
msgstr "Decrepit bones, heaped in a pile …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya30"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.59"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc27"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:30.1"
msgid "Aṭṭhikāni pūtīni cuṇṇakajātāni."
msgstr "Bones rotted and crumbled to powder."

msgctxt "mn10:30.2"
msgid "So imameva kāyaṃ upasaṃharati:"
msgstr "They’d compare it with their own body:"

msgctxt "mn10:30.3"
msgid "‘ayampi kho kāyo evaṃdhammo evaṃbhāvī evaṃanatīto’ti. (9)"
msgstr ""
"‘This body is also of that same nature, that same kind, and cannot go beyond "
"that.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya31"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc28"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:31.1"
msgid ""
"Iti ajjhattaṃ vā kāye kāyānupassī viharati, bahiddhā vā kāye kāyānupassī "
"viharati, ajjhattabahiddhā vā kāye kāyānupassī viharati;"
msgstr ""
"And so they meditate observing an aspect of the body internally, externally, "
"and both internally and externally."

msgctxt "mn10:31.2"
msgid ""
"samudayadhammānupassī vā kāyasmiṃ viharati, vayadhammānupassī vā kāyasmiṃ "
"viharati, samudayavayadhammānupassī vā kāyasmiṃ viharati."
msgstr ""
"They meditate observing the body as liable to originate, as liable to "
"vanish, and as liable to both originate and vanish."

msgctxt "mn10:31.3"
msgid ""
"‘Atthi kāyo’ti vā panassa sati paccupaṭṭhitā hoti. Yāvadeva ñāṇamattāya "
"paṭissatimattāya anissito ca viharati, na ca kiñci loke upādiyati."
msgstr ""
"Or mindfulness is established that the body exists, to the extent necessary "
"for knowledge and mindfulness. They meditate independent, not grasping at "
"anything in the world."

msgctxt "mn10:31.4"
msgid "Evampi kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati."
msgstr ""
"That too is how a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn10:31.5"
msgid "Navasivathikapabbaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn10:31.6"
msgid "Cuddasakāyānupassanā niṭṭhitā."
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "mn10:31.7"
msgid "2. Vedanānupassanā"
msgstr "2. Observing the Feelings"

#. </h2><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya32"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc29"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:32.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vedanāsu vedanānupassī viharati?"
msgstr "And how does a mendicant meditate observing an aspect of feelings?"

#. VAR: sukhaṃ vā → sukhaṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "mn10:32.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sukhaṃ vā vedanaṃ vedayamāno ‘sukhaṃ vedanaṃ "
"vedayāmī’ti pajānāti. (1)"
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant who feels a pleasant feeling knows: ‘I feel a pleasant "
"feeling.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc30"></a>
#. VAR: Dukkhaṃ vā → dukkhaṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "mn10:32.3"
msgid ""
"Dukkhaṃ vā vedanaṃ vedayamāno ‘dukkhaṃ vedanaṃ vedayāmī’ti pajānāti. (2)"
msgstr ""
"When they feel a painful feeling, they know: ‘I feel a painful feeling.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc31"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:32.4"
msgid ""
"Adukkhamasukhaṃ vā vedanaṃ vedayamāno ‘adukkhamasukhaṃ vedanaṃ vedayāmī’ti "
"pajānāti. (3)"
msgstr ""
"When they feel a neutral feeling, they know: ‘I feel a neutral feeling.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc32"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:32.5"
msgid ""
"Sāmisaṃ vā sukhaṃ vedanaṃ vedayamāno ‘sāmisaṃ sukhaṃ vedanaṃ vedayāmī’ti "
"pajānāti. (4)"
msgstr ""
"When they feel a carnal pleasant feeling, they know: ‘I feel a carnal "
"pleasant feeling.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc33"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:32.6"
msgid ""
"Nirāmisaṃ vā sukhaṃ vedanaṃ vedayamāno ‘nirāmisaṃ sukhaṃ vedanaṃ vedayāmī’ti "
"pajānāti. (5)"
msgstr ""
"When they feel a spiritual pleasant feeling, they know: ‘I feel a spiritual "
"pleasant feeling.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc34"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:32.7"
msgid ""
"Sāmisaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vedanaṃ vedayamāno ‘sāmisaṃ dukkhaṃ vedanaṃ vedayāmī’ti "
"pajānāti. (6)"
msgstr ""
"When they feel a carnal painful feeling, they know: ‘I feel a carnal painful "
"feeling.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc35"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:32.8"
msgid ""
"Nirāmisaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vedanaṃ vedayamāno ‘nirāmisaṃ dukkhaṃ vedanaṃ vedayāmī’"
"ti pajānāti. (7)"
msgstr ""
"When they feel a spiritual painful feeling, they know: ‘I feel a spiritual "
"painful feeling.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc36"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:32.9"
msgid ""
"Sāmisaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vedanaṃ vedayamāno ‘sāmisaṃ adukkhamasukhaṃ "
"vedanaṃ vedayāmī’ti pajānāti. (8)"
msgstr ""
"When they feel a carnal neutral feeling, they know: ‘I feel a carnal neutral "
"feeling.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc37"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:32.10"
msgid ""
"Nirāmisaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vedanaṃ vedayamāno ‘nirāmisaṃ adukkhamasukhaṃ "
"vedanaṃ vedayāmī’ti pajānāti. (9)"
msgstr ""
"When they feel a spiritual neutral feeling, they know: ‘I feel a spiritual "
"neutral feeling.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya33"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc38"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:33.1"
msgid ""
"Iti ajjhattaṃ vā vedanāsu vedanānupassī viharati, bahiddhā vā vedanāsu "
"vedanānupassī viharati, ajjhattabahiddhā vā vedanāsu vedanānupassī viharati;"
msgstr ""
"And so they meditate observing an aspect of the feelings internally, "
"externally, and both internally and externally."

msgctxt "mn10:33.2"
msgid ""
"samudayadhammānupassī vā vedanāsu viharati, vayadhammānupassī vā vedanāsu "
"viharati, samudayavayadhammānupassī vā vedanāsu viharati."
msgstr ""
"They meditate observing the body as liable to originate, as liable to "
"vanish, and as liable to both originate and vanish."

msgctxt "mn10:33.3"
msgid "‘Atthi vedanā’ti vā panassa sati paccupaṭṭhitā hoti."
msgstr "Or mindfulness is established that feelings exist,"

msgctxt "mn10:33.4"
msgid ""
"Yāvadeva ñāṇamattāya paṭissatimattāya anissito ca viharati, na ca kiñci loke "
"upādiyati."
msgstr ""
"to the extent necessary for knowledge and mindfulness. They meditate "
"independent, not grasping at anything in the world."

msgctxt "mn10:33.5"
msgid "Evampi kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vedanāsu vedanānupassī viharati."
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of feelings."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn10:33.6"
msgid "Vedanānupassanā niṭṭhitā."
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "mn10:33.7"
msgid "3. Cittānupassanā"
msgstr "3. Observing the Mind"

#. </h2><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya34"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc39"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:34.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu citte cittānupassī viharati?"
msgstr "And how does a mendicant meditate observing an aspect of the mind?"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "mn10:34.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sarāgaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘sarāgaṃ cittan’ti pajānāti. (1) "
"Vītarāgaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘vītarāgaṃ cittan’ti pajānāti. (2) Sadosaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘"
"sadosaṃ cittan’ti pajānāti. (3) Vītadosaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘vītadosaṃ cittan’ti "
"pajānāti. (4) Samohaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘samohaṃ cittan’ti pajānāti. (5) Vītamohaṃ "
"vā cittaṃ ‘vītamohaṃ cittan’ti pajānāti. (6) Saṅkhittaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘"
"saṅkhittaṃ cittan’ti pajānāti. (7) Vikkhittaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘vikkhittaṃ cittan’"
"ti pajānāti. (8) Mahaggataṃ vā cittaṃ ‘mahaggataṃ cittan’ti pajānāti. (9) "
"Amahaggataṃ vā cittaṃ ‘amahaggataṃ cittan’ti pajānāti. (10) Sauttaraṃ vā "
"cittaṃ ‘sauttaraṃ cittan’ti pajānāti. (11) Anuttaraṃ vā cittaṃ ‘anuttaraṃ "
"cittan’ti pajānāti. (12) Samāhitaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘samāhitaṃ cittan’ti pajānāti. "
"(13) Asamāhitaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘asamāhitaṃ cittan’ti pajānāti. (14) Vimuttaṃ vā "
"cittaṃ ‘vimuttaṃ cittan’ti pajānāti. (15) Avimuttaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘avimuttaṃ "
"cittan’ti pajānāti. (16)"
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant knows mind with greed as ‘mind with greed,’ and mind "
"without greed as ‘mind without greed.’ They know mind with hate as ‘mind "
"with hate,’ and mind without hate as ‘mind without hate.’ They know mind "
"with delusion as ‘mind with delusion,’ and mind without delusion as ‘mind "
"without delusion.’ They know contracted mind as ‘contracted mind,’ and "
"scattered mind as ‘scattered mind.’ They know expansive mind as ‘expansive "
"mind,’ and unexpansive mind as ‘unexpansive mind.’ They know mind that is "
"not supreme as ‘mind that is not supreme,’ and mind that is supreme as ‘mind "
"that is supreme.’ They know mind immersed in samādhi as ‘mind immersed in "
"samādhi,’ and mind not immersed in samādhi as ‘mind not immersed in samādhi.’"
" They know freed mind as ‘freed mind,’ and unfreed mind as ‘unfreed mind.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya35"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.60"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc55"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:35.1"
msgid ""
"Iti ajjhattaṃ vā citte cittānupassī viharati, bahiddhā vā citte cittānupassī "
"viharati, ajjhattabahiddhā vā citte cittānupassī viharati;"
msgstr ""
"And so they meditate observing an aspect of the mind internally, externally, "
"and both internally and externally."

msgctxt "mn10:35.2"
msgid ""
"samudayadhammānupassī vā cittasmiṃ viharati, vayadhammānupassī vā cittasmiṃ "
"viharati, samudayavayadhammānupassī vā cittasmiṃ viharati."
msgstr ""
"They meditate observing the mind as liable to originate, as liable to "
"vanish, and as liable to both originate and vanish."

msgctxt "mn10:35.3"
msgid ""
"‘Atthi cittan’ti vā panassa sati paccupaṭṭhitā hoti. Yāvadeva ñāṇamattāya "
"paṭissatimattāya anissito ca viharati, na ca kiñci loke upādiyati."
msgstr ""
"Or mindfulness is established that the mind exists, to the extent necessary "
"for knowledge and mindfulness. They meditate independent, not grasping at "
"anything in the world."

msgctxt "mn10:35.4"
msgid "Evampi kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu citte cittānupassī viharati."
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the mind."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn10:35.5"
msgid "Cittānupassanā niṭṭhitā."
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "mn10:35.6"
msgid "4. Dhammānupassanā"
msgstr "4. Observing Principles"

#. </h2><h3>
msgctxt "mn10:35.7"
msgid "4.1. Dhammānupassanānīvaraṇapabba"
msgstr "4.1. The Hindrances"

#. </h3><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya36"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc56"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:36.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati?"
msgstr "And how does a mendicant meditate observing an aspect of principles?"

msgctxt "mn10:36.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati pañcasu nīvaraṇesu."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of principles with "
"respect to the five hindrances."

msgctxt "mn10:36.3"
msgid ""
"Kathañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati pañcasu "
"nīvaraṇesu?"
msgstr ""
"And how does a mendicant meditate observing an aspect of principles with "
"respect to the five hindrances?"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc57"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:36.4"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu santaṃ vā ajjhattaṃ kāmacchandaṃ ‘atthi me "
"ajjhattaṃ kāmacchando’ti pajānāti, asantaṃ vā ajjhattaṃ kāmacchandaṃ ‘natthi "
"me ajjhattaṃ kāmacchando’ti pajānāti; yathā ca anuppannassa kāmacchandassa "
"uppādo hoti tañca pajānāti, yathā ca uppannassa kāmacchandassa pahānaṃ hoti "
"tañca pajānāti, yathā ca pahīnassa kāmacchandassa āyatiṃ anuppādo hoti tañca "
"pajānāti. (1)"
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant who has sensual desire in them understands: ‘I have "
"sensual desire in me.’ When they don’t have sensual desire in them, they "
"understand: ‘I don’t have sensual desire in me.’ They understand how sensual "
"desire arises; how, when it’s already arisen, it’s given up; and how, once "
"it’s given up, it doesn’t arise again in the future."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc58"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:36.5"
msgid ""
"Santaṃ vā ajjhattaṃ byāpādaṃ ‘atthi me ajjhattaṃ byāpādo’ti pajānāti, "
"asantaṃ vā ajjhattaṃ byāpādaṃ ‘natthi me ajjhattaṃ byāpādo’ti pajānāti; "
"yathā ca anuppannassa byāpādassa uppādo hoti tañca pajānāti, yathā ca "
"uppannassa byāpādassa pahānaṃ hoti tañca pajānāti, yathā ca pahīnassa "
"byāpādassa āyatiṃ anuppādo hoti tañca pajānāti. (2)"
msgstr ""
"When they have ill will in them, they understand: ‘I have ill will in me.’ "
"When they don’t have ill will in them, they understand: ‘I don’t have ill "
"will in me.’ They understand how ill will arises; how, when it’s already "
"arisen, it’s given up; and how, once it’s given up, it doesn’t arise again "
"in the future."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc59"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:36.6"
msgid ""
"Santaṃ vā ajjhattaṃ thinamiddhaṃ ‘atthi me ajjhattaṃ thinamiddhan’ti "
"pajānāti, asantaṃ vā ajjhattaṃ thinamiddhaṃ ‘natthi me ajjhattaṃ "
"thinamiddhan’ti pajānāti, yathā ca anuppannassa thinamiddhassa uppādo hoti "
"tañca pajānāti, yathā ca uppannassa thinamiddhassa pahānaṃ hoti tañca "
"pajānāti, yathā ca pahīnassa thinamiddhassa āyatiṃ anuppādo hoti tañca "
"pajānāti. (3)"
msgstr ""
"When they have dullness and drowsiness in them, they understand: ‘I have "
"dullness and drowsiness in me.’ When they don’t have dullness and drowsiness "
"in them, they understand: ‘I don’t have dullness and drowsiness in me.’ They "
"understand how dullness and drowsiness arise; how, when they’ve already "
"arisen, they’re given up; and how, once they’re given up, they don’t arise "
"again in the future."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc60"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:36.7"
msgid ""
"Santaṃ vā ajjhattaṃ uddhaccakukkuccaṃ ‘atthi me ajjhattaṃ uddhaccakukkuccan’"
"ti pajānāti, asantaṃ vā ajjhattaṃ uddhaccakukkuccaṃ ‘natthi me ajjhattaṃ "
"uddhaccakukkuccan’ti pajānāti; yathā ca anuppannassa uddhaccakukkuccassa "
"uppādo hoti tañca pajānāti, yathā ca uppannassa uddhaccakukkuccassa pahānaṃ "
"hoti tañca pajānāti, yathā ca pahīnassa uddhaccakukkuccassa āyatiṃ anuppādo "
"hoti tañca pajānāti. (4)"
msgstr ""
"When they have restlessness and remorse in them, they understand: ‘I have "
"restlessness and remorse in me.’ When they don’t have restlessness and "
"remorse in them, they understand: ‘I don’t have restlessness and remorse in "
"me.’ They understand how restlessness and remorse arise; how, when they’ve "
"already arisen, they’re given up; and how, once they’re given up, they don’t "
"arise again in the future."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc61"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:36.8"
msgid ""
"Santaṃ vā ajjhattaṃ vicikicchaṃ ‘atthi me ajjhattaṃ vicikicchā’ti pajānāti, "
"asantaṃ vā ajjhattaṃ vicikicchaṃ ‘natthi me ajjhattaṃ vicikicchā’ti pajānāti;"
" yathā ca anuppannāya vicikicchāya uppādo hoti tañca pajānāti, yathā ca "
"uppannāya vicikicchāya pahānaṃ hoti tañca pajānāti, yathā ca pahīnāya "
"vicikicchāya āyatiṃ anuppādo hoti tañca pajānāti. (5)"
msgstr ""
"When they have doubt in them, they understand: ‘I have doubt in me.’ When "
"they don’t have doubt in them, they understand: ‘I don’t have doubt in me.’ "
"They understand how doubt arises; how, when it’s already arisen, it’s given "
"up; and how, once it’s given up, it doesn’t arise again in the future."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya37"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc62"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:37.1"
msgid ""
"Iti ajjhattaṃ vā dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati, bahiddhā vā dhammesu "
"dhammānupassī viharati, ajjhattabahiddhā vā dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati;"
msgstr ""
"And so they meditate observing an aspect of principles internally, "
"externally, and both internally and externally."

msgctxt "mn10:37.2"
msgid ""
"samudayadhammānupassī vā dhammesu viharati, vayadhammānupassī vā dhammesu "
"viharati, samudayavayadhammānupassī vā dhammesu viharati."
msgstr ""
"They meditate observing the principles as liable to originate, as liable to "
"vanish, and as liable to both originate and vanish."

msgctxt "mn10:37.3"
msgid "‘Atthi dhammā’ti vā panassa sati paccupaṭṭhitā hoti."
msgstr "Or mindfulness is established that principles exist,"

msgctxt "mn10:37.4"
msgid ""
"Yāvadeva ñāṇamattāya paṭissatimattāya anissito ca viharati, na ca kiñci loke "
"upādiyati."
msgstr ""
"to the extent necessary for knowledge and mindfulness. They meditate "
"independent, not grasping at anything in the world."

msgctxt "mn10:37.5"
msgid ""
"Evampi kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati pañcasu "
"nīvaraṇesu."
msgstr ""
"That’s how a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of principles with "
"respect to the five hindrances."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn10:37.6"
msgid "Nīvaraṇapabbaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "mn10:37.7"
msgid "4.2. Dhammānupassanākhandhapabba"
msgstr "4.2. The Aggregates"

#. </h3><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya38"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.61"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc63"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:38.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati pañcasu "
"upādānakkhandhesu."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of principles with "
"respect to the five grasping aggregates."

msgctxt "mn10:38.2"
msgid ""
"Kathañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati pañcasu "
"upādānakkhandhesu?"
msgstr ""
"And how does a mendicant meditate observing an aspect of principles with "
"respect to the five grasping aggregates?"

msgctxt "mn10:38.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu:"
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant contemplates:"

msgctxt "mn10:38.4"
msgid "‘iti rūpaṃ, iti rūpassa samudayo, iti rūpassa atthaṅgamo;"
msgstr "‘Such is form, such is the origin of form, such is the ending of form."

msgctxt "mn10:38.5"
msgid "iti vedanā, iti vedanāya samudayo, iti vedanāya atthaṅgamo;"
msgstr ""
"Such is feeling, such is the origin of feeling, such is the ending of "
"feeling."

msgctxt "mn10:38.6"
msgid "iti saññā, iti saññāya samudayo, iti saññāya atthaṅgamo;"
msgstr ""
"Such is perception, such is the origin of perception, such is the ending of "
"perception."

msgctxt "mn10:38.7"
msgid "iti saṅkhārā, iti saṅkhārānaṃ samudayo, iti saṅkhārānaṃ atthaṅgamo;"
msgstr ""
"Such are choices, such is the origin of choices, such is the ending of "
"choices."

msgctxt "mn10:38.8"
msgid "iti viññāṇaṃ, iti viññāṇassa samudayo, iti viññāṇassa atthaṅgamo’ti;"
msgstr ""
"Such is consciousness, such is the origin of consciousness, such is the "
"ending of consciousness.’"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya39"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:39.1"
msgid ""
"iti ajjhattaṃ vā dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati, bahiddhā vā dhammesu "
"dhammānupassī viharati, ajjhattabahiddhā vā dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati;"
msgstr "And so they meditate observing an aspect of principles internally …"

msgctxt "mn10:39.2"
msgid ""
"samudayadhammānupassī vā dhammesu viharati, vayadhammānupassī vā dhammesu "
"viharati, samudayavayadhammānupassī vā dhammesu viharati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn10:39.3"
msgid "‘Atthi dhammā’ti vā panassa sati paccupaṭṭhitā hoti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn10:39.4"
msgid ""
"Yāvadeva ñāṇamattāya paṭissatimattāya anissito ca viharati, na ca kiñci loke "
"upādiyati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn10:39.5"
msgid ""
"Evampi kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati pañcasu "
"upādānakkhandhesu."
msgstr ""
"That’s how a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of principles with "
"respect to the five grasping aggregates."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn10:39.6"
msgid "Khandhapabbaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "mn10:39.7"
msgid "4.3. Dhammānupassanāāyatanapabba"
msgstr "4.3. The Sense Fields"

#. </h3><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya40"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc64"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:40.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati chasu "
"ajjhattikabāhiresu āyatanesu."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of principles with "
"respect to the six interior and exterior sense fields."

msgctxt "mn10:40.2"
msgid ""
"Kathañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati chasu "
"ajjhattikabāhiresu āyatanesu?"
msgstr ""
"And how does a mendicant meditate observing an aspect of principles with "
"respect to the six interior and exterior sense fields?"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc65"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:40.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cakkhuñca pajānāti, rūpe ca pajānāti, yañca "
"tadubhayaṃ paṭicca uppajjati saṃyojanaṃ tañca pajānāti, yathā ca "
"anuppannassa saṃyojanassa uppādo hoti tañca pajānāti, yathā ca uppannassa "
"saṃyojanassa pahānaṃ hoti tañca pajānāti, yathā ca pahīnassa saṃyojanassa "
"āyatiṃ anuppādo hoti tañca pajānāti. (1)"
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant understands the eye, sights, and the fetter that "
"arises dependent on both of these. They understand how the fetter that has "
"not arisen comes to arise; how the arisen fetter comes to be abandoned; and "
"how the abandoned fetter comes to not rise again in the future."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc66"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:40.4"
msgid ""
"Sotañca pajānāti, sadde ca pajānāti, yañca tadubhayaṃ paṭicca uppajjati "
"saṃyojanaṃ tañca pajānāti, yathā ca anuppannassa saṃyojanassa uppādo hoti "
"tañca pajānāti, yathā ca uppannassa saṃyojanassa pahānaṃ hoti tañca "
"pajānāti, yathā ca pahīnassa saṃyojanassa āyatiṃ anuppādo hoti tañca "
"pajānāti. (2)"
msgstr "They understand the ear, sounds, and the fetter …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc67"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:40.5"
msgid ""
"Ghānañca pajānāti, gandhe ca pajānāti, yañca tadubhayaṃ paṭicca uppajjati "
"saṃyojanaṃ tañca pajānāti, yathā ca anuppannassa saṃyojanassa uppādo hoti "
"tañca pajānāti, yathā ca uppannassa saṃyojanassa pahānaṃ hoti tañca "
"pajānāti, yathā ca pahīnassa saṃyojanassa āyatiṃ anuppādo hoti tañca "
"pajānāti. (3)"
msgstr "They understand the nose, smells, and the fetter …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc68"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:40.6"
msgid ""
"Jivhañca pajānāti, rase ca pajānāti, yañca tadubhayaṃ paṭicca uppajjati "
"saṃyojanaṃ tañca pajānāti, yathā ca anuppannassa saṃyojanassa uppādo hoti "
"tañca pajānāti, yathā ca uppannassa saṃyojanassa pahānaṃ hoti tañca "
"pajānāti, yathā ca pahīnassa saṃyojanassa āyatiṃ anuppādo hoti tañca "
"pajānāti. (4)"
msgstr "They understand the tongue, tastes, and the fetter …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc69"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:40.7"
msgid ""
"Kāyañca pajānāti, phoṭṭhabbe ca pajānāti, yañca tadubhayaṃ paṭicca uppajjati "
"saṃyojanaṃ tañca pajānāti, yathā ca anuppannassa saṃyojanassa uppādo hoti "
"tañca pajānāti, yathā ca uppannassa saṃyojanassa pahānaṃ hoti tañca "
"pajānāti, yathā ca pahīnassa saṃyojanassa āyatiṃ anuppādo hoti tañca "
"pajānāti. (5)"
msgstr "They understand the body, touches, and the fetter …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc70"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:40.8"
msgid ""
"Manañca pajānāti, dhamme ca pajānāti, yañca tadubhayaṃ paṭicca uppajjati "
"saṃyojanaṃ tañca pajānāti, yathā ca anuppannassa saṃyojanassa uppādo hoti "
"tañca pajānāti, yathā ca uppannassa saṃyojanassa pahānaṃ hoti tañca "
"pajānāti, yathā ca pahīnassa saṃyojanassa āyatiṃ anuppādo hoti tañca "
"pajānāti. (6)"
msgstr ""
"They understand the mind, thoughts, and the fetter that arises dependent on "
"both of these. They understand how the fetter that has not arisen comes to "
"arise; how the arisen fetter comes to be abandoned; and how the abandoned "
"fetter comes to not rise again in the future."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya41"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc71"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:41.1"
msgid ""
"Iti ajjhattaṃ vā dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati, bahiddhā vā dhammesu "
"dhammānupassī viharati, ajjhattabahiddhā vā dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati;"
msgstr "And so they meditate observing an aspect of principles internally …"

msgctxt "mn10:41.2"
msgid ""
"samudayadhammānupassī vā dhammesu viharati, vayadhammānupassī vā dhammesu "
"viharati, samudayavayadhammānupassī vā dhammesu viharati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn10:41.3"
msgid "‘Atthi dhammā’ti vā panassa sati paccupaṭṭhitā hoti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn10:41.4"
msgid ""
"Yāvadeva ñāṇamattāya paṭissatimattāya anissito ca viharati na ca kiñci loke "
"upādiyati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn10:41.5"
msgid ""
"Evampi kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati chasu "
"ajjhattikabāhiresu āyatanesu."
msgstr ""
"That’s how a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of principles with "
"respect to the six internal and external sense fields."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn10:41.6"
msgid "Āyatanapabbaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "mn10:41.7"
msgid "4.4. Dhammānupassanābojjhaṅgapabba"
msgstr "4.4. The Awakening Factors"

#. </h3><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya42"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.62"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc72"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:42.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati sattasu "
"bojjhaṅgesu."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of principles with "
"respect to the seven awakening factors."

msgctxt "mn10:42.2"
msgid ""
"Kathañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati sattasu "
"bojjhaṅgesu?"
msgstr ""
"And how does a mendicant meditate observing an aspect of principles with "
"respect to the seven awakening factors?"

msgctxt "mn10:42.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu santaṃ vā ajjhattaṃ satisambojjhaṅgaṃ ‘atthi me "
"ajjhattaṃ satisambojjhaṅgo’ti pajānāti, asantaṃ vā ajjhattaṃ "
"satisambojjhaṅgaṃ ‘natthi me ajjhattaṃ satisambojjhaṅgo’ti pajānāti, yathā "
"ca anuppannassa satisambojjhaṅgassa uppādo hoti tañca pajānāti, yathā ca "
"uppannassa satisambojjhaṅgassa bhāvanāya pāripūrī hoti tañca pajānāti. (1)"
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant who has the awakening factor of mindfulness in them "
"understands: ‘I have the awakening factor of mindfulness in me.’ When they "
"don’t have the awakening factor of mindfulness in them, they understand: ‘I "
"don’t have the awakening factor of mindfulness in me.’ They understand how "
"the awakening factor of mindfulness that has not arisen comes to arise; and "
"how the awakening factor of mindfulness that has arisen becomes fulfilled by "
"development."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc73"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:42.4"
msgid ""
"Santaṃ vā ajjhattaṃ dhammavicayasambojjhaṅgaṃ ‘atthi me ajjhattaṃ "
"dhammavicayasambojjhaṅgo’ti pajānāti, asantaṃ vā ajjhattaṃ "
"dhammavicayasambojjhaṅgaṃ ‘natthi me ajjhattaṃ dhammavicayasambojjhaṅgo’ti "
"pajānāti, yathā ca anuppannassa dhammavicayasambojjhaṅgassa uppādo hoti "
"tañca pajānāti, yathā ca uppannassa dhammavicayasambojjhaṅgassa bhāvanāya "
"pāripūrī hoti tañca pajānāti. (2)"
msgstr "When they have the awakening factor of investigation of principles …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc74"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:42.5"
msgid ""
"Santaṃ vā ajjhattaṃ vīriyasambojjhaṅgaṃ ‘atthi me ajjhattaṃ "
"vīriyasambojjhaṅgo’ti pajānāti, asantaṃ vā ajjhattaṃ vīriyasambojjhaṅgaṃ ‘"
"natthi me ajjhattaṃ vīriyasambojjhaṅgo’ti pajānāti, yathā ca anuppannassa "
"vīriyasambojjhaṅgassa uppādo hoti tañca pajānāti, yathā ca uppannassa "
"vīriyasambojjhaṅgassa bhāvanāya pāripūrī hoti tañca pajānāti. (3)"
msgstr "energy …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc75"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:42.6"
msgid ""
"Santaṃ vā ajjhattaṃ pītisambojjhaṅgaṃ ‘atthi me ajjhattaṃ pītisambojjhaṅgo’"
"ti pajānāti, asantaṃ vā ajjhattaṃ pītisambojjhaṅgaṃ ‘natthi me ajjhattaṃ "
"pītisambojjhaṅgo’ti pajānāti, yathā ca anuppannassa pītisambojjhaṅgassa "
"uppādo hoti tañca pajānāti, yathā ca uppannassa pītisambojjhaṅgassa "
"bhāvanāya pāripūrī hoti tañca pajānāti. (4)"
msgstr "rapture …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc76"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:42.7"
msgid ""
"Santaṃ vā ajjhattaṃ passaddhisambojjhaṅgaṃ ‘atthi me ajjhattaṃ "
"passaddhisambojjhaṅgo’ti pajānāti, asantaṃ vā ajjhattaṃ "
"passaddhisambojjhaṅgaṃ ‘natthi me ajjhattaṃ passaddhisambojjhaṅgo’ti "
"pajānāti, yathā ca anuppannassa passaddhisambojjhaṅgassa uppādo hoti tañca "
"pajānāti, yathā ca uppannassa passaddhisambojjhaṅgassa bhāvanāya pāripūrī "
"hoti tañca pajānāti. (5)"
msgstr "tranquility …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc77"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:42.8"
msgid ""
"Santaṃ vā ajjhattaṃ samādhisambojjhaṅgaṃ ‘atthi me ajjhattaṃ "
"samādhisambojjhaṅgo’ti pajānāti, asantaṃ vā ajjhattaṃ samādhisambojjhaṅgaṃ ‘"
"natthi me ajjhattaṃ samādhisambojjhaṅgo’ti pajānāti, yathā ca anuppannassa "
"samādhisambojjhaṅgassa uppādo hoti tañca pajānāti, yathā ca uppannassa "
"samādhisambojjhaṅgassa bhāvanāya pāripūrī hoti tañca pajānāti. (6)"
msgstr "immersion …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc78"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:42.9"
msgid ""
"Santaṃ vā ajjhattaṃ upekkhāsambojjhaṅgaṃ ‘atthi me ajjhattaṃ "
"upekkhāsambojjhaṅgo’ti pajānāti, asantaṃ vā ajjhattaṃ upekkhāsambojjhaṅgaṃ ‘"
"natthi me ajjhattaṃ upekkhāsambojjhaṅgo’ti pajānāti, yathā ca anuppannassa "
"upekkhāsambojjhaṅgassa uppādo hoti tañca pajānāti, yathā ca uppannassa "
"upekkhāsambojjhaṅgassa bhāvanāya pāripūrī hoti tañca pajānāti. (7)"
msgstr ""
"equanimity in them, they understand: ‘I have the awakening factor of "
"equanimity in me.’ When they don’t have the awakening factor of equanimity "
"in them, they understand: ‘I don’t have the awakening factor of equanimity "
"in me.’ They understand how the awakening factor of equanimity that has not "
"arisen comes to arise; and how the awakening factor of equanimity that has "
"arisen becomes fulfilled by development."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya43"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc79"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:43.1"
msgid ""
"Iti ajjhattaṃ vā dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati, bahiddhā vā dhammesu "
"dhammānupassī viharati, ajjhattabahiddhā vā dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati;"
msgstr ""
"And so they meditate observing an aspect of principles internally, "
"externally, and both internally and externally."

msgctxt "mn10:43.2"
msgid ""
"samudayadhammānupassī vā dhammesu viharati, vayadhammānupassī vā dhammesu "
"viharati, samudayavayadhammānupassī vā dhammesu viharati."
msgstr ""
"They meditate observing the principles as liable to originate, as liable to "
"vanish, and as liable to both originate and vanish."

msgctxt "mn10:43.3"
msgid "‘Atthi dhammā’ti vā panassa sati paccupaṭṭhitā hoti."
msgstr "Or mindfulness is established that principles exist,"

msgctxt "mn10:43.4"
msgid ""
"Yāvadeva ñāṇamattāya paṭissatimattāya anissito ca viharati, na ca kiñci loke "
"upādiyati."
msgstr ""
"to the extent necessary for knowledge and mindfulness. They meditate "
"independent, not grasping at anything in the world."

msgctxt "mn10:43.5"
msgid ""
"Evampi kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati sattasu "
"bojjhaṅgesu."
msgstr ""
"That’s how a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of principles with "
"respect to the seven awakening factors."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn10:43.6"
msgid "Bojjhaṅgapabbaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "mn10:43.7"
msgid "4.5. Dhammānupassanāsaccapabba"
msgstr "4.5. The Truths"

#. </h3><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya44"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc80"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:44.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati catūsu "
"ariyasaccesu."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of principles with "
"respect to the four noble truths."

msgctxt "mn10:44.2"
msgid ""
"Kathañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati catūsu "
"ariyasaccesu?"
msgstr ""
"And how does a mendicant meditate observing an aspect of principles with "
"respect to the four noble truths?"

msgctxt "mn10:44.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ "
"dukkhasamudayo’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodho’ti yathābhūtaṃ "
"pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant truly understands: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the "
"origin of suffering’ … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the "
"practice that leads to the cessation of suffering.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya45"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc128"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:45.1"
msgid ""
"Iti ajjhattaṃ vā dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati, bahiddhā vā dhammesu "
"dhammānupassī viharati, ajjhattabahiddhā vā dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati;"
msgstr ""
"And so they meditate observing an aspect of principles internally, "
"externally, and both internally and externally."

msgctxt "mn10:45.2"
msgid ""
"samudayadhammānupassī vā dhammesu viharati, vayadhammānupassī vā dhammesu "
"viharati, samudayavayadhammānupassī vā dhammesu viharati."
msgstr ""
"They meditate observing the principles as liable to originate, as liable to "
"vanish, and as liable to both originate and vanish."

msgctxt "mn10:45.3"
msgid "‘Atthi dhammā’ti vā panassa sati paccupaṭṭhitā hoti."
msgstr "Or mindfulness is established that principles exist,"

msgctxt "mn10:45.4"
msgid ""
"Yāvadeva ñāṇamattāya paṭissatimattāya anissito ca viharati, na ca kiñci loke "
"upādiyati."
msgstr ""
"to the extent necessary for knowledge and mindfulness. They meditate "
"independent, not grasping at anything in the world."

msgctxt "mn10:45.5"
msgid ""
"Evampi kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati catūsu "
"ariyasaccesu."
msgstr ""
"That’s how a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of principles with "
"respect to the four noble truths."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn10:45.6"
msgid "Saccapabbaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn10:45.7"
msgid "Dhammānupassanā niṭṭhitā."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya46"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc129"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:46.1"
msgid ""
"Yo hi koci, bhikkhave, ime cattāro satipaṭṭhāne evaṃ bhāveyya satta vassāni, "
"tassa dvinnaṃ phalānaṃ aññataraṃ phalaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ"
msgstr ""
"Anyone who develops these four kinds of mindfulness meditation in this way "
"for seven years can expect one of two results:"

msgctxt "mn10:46.2"
msgid "diṭṭheva dhamme aññā; sati vā upādisese anāgāmitā."
msgstr ""
"enlightenment in the present life, or if there’s something left over, non-"
"return."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.63"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc130"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:46.3"
msgid "Tiṭṭhantu, bhikkhave, satta vassāni."
msgstr "Let alone seven years,"

msgctxt "mn10:46.4"
msgid ""
"Yo hi koci, bhikkhave, ime cattāro satipaṭṭhāne evaṃ bhāveyya cha vassāni … "
"pe …"
msgstr ""
"anyone who develops these four kinds of mindfulness meditation in this way "
"for six years …"

msgctxt "mn10:46.5"
msgid "pañca vassāni …"
msgstr "five years …"

msgctxt "mn10:46.6"
msgid "cattāri vassāni …"
msgstr "four years …"

msgctxt "mn10:46.7"
msgid "tīṇi vassāni …"
msgstr "three years …"

msgctxt "mn10:46.8"
msgid "dve vassāni …"
msgstr "two years …"

msgctxt "mn10:46.9"
msgid "ekaṃ vassaṃ …"
msgstr "one year …"

msgctxt "mn10:46.10"
msgid "tiṭṭhatu, bhikkhave, ekaṃ vassaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn10:46.11"
msgid ""
"Yo hi koci, bhikkhave, ime cattāro satipaṭṭhāne evaṃ bhāveyya satta māsāni, "
"tassa dvinnaṃ phalānaṃ aññataraṃ phalaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ"
msgstr "seven months …"

msgctxt "mn10:46.12"
msgid "diṭṭheva dhamme aññā; sati vā upādisese anāgāmitā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn10:46.13"
msgid "Tiṭṭhantu, bhikkhave, satta māsāni."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn10:46.14"
msgid ""
"Yo hi koci, bhikkhave, ime cattāro satipaṭṭhāne evaṃ bhāveyya cha māsāni … "
"pe …"
msgstr "six months …"

msgctxt "mn10:46.15"
msgid "pañca māsāni …"
msgstr "five months …"

msgctxt "mn10:46.16"
msgid "cattāri māsāni …"
msgstr "four months …"

msgctxt "mn10:46.17"
msgid "tīṇi māsāni …"
msgstr "three months …"

msgctxt "mn10:46.18"
msgid "dve māsāni …"
msgstr "two months …"

msgctxt "mn10:46.19"
msgid "ekaṃ māsaṃ …"
msgstr "one month …"

msgctxt "mn10:46.20"
msgid "aḍḍhamāsaṃ …"
msgstr "a fortnight …"

msgctxt "mn10:46.21"
msgid "tiṭṭhatu, bhikkhave, aḍḍhamāso."
msgstr "Let alone a fortnight,"

msgctxt "mn10:46.22"
msgid ""
"Yo hi koci, bhikkhave, ime cattāro satipaṭṭhāne evaṃ bhāveyya sattāhaṃ, "
"tassa dvinnaṃ phalānaṃ aññataraṃ phalaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ "
msgstr ""
"anyone who develops these four kinds of mindfulness meditation in this way "
"for seven days can expect one of two results: "

msgctxt "mn10:46.23"
msgid "diṭṭheva dhamme aññā sati vā upādisese anāgāmitāti."
msgstr ""
"enlightenment in the present life, or if there’s something left over, non-"
"return."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya47"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc131"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:47.1"
msgid ""
"‘Ekāyano ayaṃ, bhikkhave, maggo sattānaṃ visuddhiyā sokaparidevānaṃ "
"samatikkamāya dukkhadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamāya ñāyassa adhigamāya nibbānassa "
"sacchikiriyāya yadidaṃ cattāro satipaṭṭhānā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘The four kinds of mindfulness meditation are the path to convergence. They "
"are in order to purify sentient beings, to get past sorrow and crying, to "
"make an end of pain and sadness, to complete the procedure, and to realize "
"extinguishment.’"

msgctxt "mn10:47.2"
msgid "Iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ, idametaṃ paṭicca vuttan”ti."
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc132"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:47.3"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "mn10:47.4"
msgid "Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti."
msgstr "Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn10:47.5"
msgid "Satipaṭṭhānasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dasamaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "mn10:47.6"
msgid "Mūlapariyāyavaggo niṭṭhito paṭhamo."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc133"></a>
msgctxt "mn10:47.7"
msgid "Mūlasusaṃvaradhammadāyādā,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn10:47.8"
msgid "Bheravānaṅgaṇākaṅkheyyavatthaṃ;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn10:47.9"
msgid "Sallekhasammādiṭṭhisatipaṭṭhaṃ,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn10:47.10"
msgid "Vaggavaro asamo susamatto."
msgstr ""
